# Supabase Queues — Complete Reference

Supabase Queues is a Dashboard Module built on pgmq — durable message queues with guaranteed delivery inside Postgres.

---

## Step 1 — Enable Queues (REQUIRED — easy to miss)

```
Supabase Dashboard → Integrations → Queues → Enable

This creates the pgmq_public schema with PostgREST-accessible wrapper functions.
WITHOUT this step: supabase.rpc('send', ...) fails with "function not found".
```

After enabling, create your first queue:
```
Dashboard → Integrations → Queues → Add Queue
  Name: embeddings_queue (or any name)
  Type: Basic (durable) OR Unlogged (fast, non-durable)
```

---

## Queue Types — Choose Before Creating

| | Basic Queue | Unlogged Queue |
|---|---|---|
| Durability | WAL-logged — survives DB restart/crash | Not WAL-logged — messages LOST on crash |
| Performance | Standard | ~2-3x faster writes |
| Use for | Embedding jobs, email sends, critical tasks | Ephemeral notifications, cache invalidation |
| Change type? | Cannot change — must recreate | Cannot change — must recreate |

---

## Critical: Use pgmq_public Schema for All RPC Calls

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — pgmq functions are in pgmq_public schema, not public
const { data } = await supabase.rpc('send', { queue_name: 'my_queue', message: {} })
// Error: "Could not find the function public.send"

// ✅ CORRECT — switch schema before calling
const { data } = await supabase
  .schema('pgmq_public')
  .rpc('send', {
    queue_name: 'embeddings_queue',
    message: { document_id: 123, content: 'hello' },
  })

// Also applies to all other queue operations:
// .schema('pgmq_public').rpc('read', ...)
// .schema('pgmq_public').rpc('delete', ...)
// .schema('pgmq_public').rpc('archive', ...)
```

