## Long-Poll — Block Until Message Arrives

More efficient than polling when queues are often empty.

```typescript
// Block for up to 5 seconds waiting for a message — no message = returns empty
const { data: messages } = await supabase
  .schema('pgmq_public')
  .rpc('read_with_poll', {
    queue_name: 'embeddings_queue',
    vt: 60,
    qty: 10,
    max_poll_seconds: 5,         // wait up to 5s for a message
    poll_interval_ms: 100,        // check every 100ms
  })
// Returns immediately when a message arrives
// Returns empty array after max_poll_seconds with no messages
```

