## Client-Side Queue Access (RLS Required)

To allow browser clients to add messages to a queue (e.g., user submits a job):

```sql
-- 1. Enable RLS on the queue table (replace 'embeddings_queue' with your queue name)
ALTER TABLE pgmq.q_embeddings_queue ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- 2. Allow authenticated users to INSERT (send messages)
CREATE POLICY "auth_users_send"
ON pgmq.q_embeddings_queue FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (auth.role() = 'authenticated');

-- 3. Only service_role can read/delete (workers use service_role)
-- (no policy needed — service_role bypasses RLS)
```

```typescript
// Client can now send messages after RLS setup
const { data: msgId } = await supabase  // browser client — uses user's JWT
  .schema('pgmq_public')
  .rpc('send', {
    queue_name: 'embeddings_queue',
    message: { text: userInput, user_id: user.id },
  })
```

