## Retry Behavior — How Automatic Retries Work

```
1. Worker reads message → message is HIDDEN for vt seconds
2. Worker succeeds → worker calls delete() → message gone
3. Worker FAILS (crash, exception) → does NOT call delete()
4. After vt seconds → message becomes VISIBLE again
5. Next worker poll reads it again → retry

read_ct field tracks how many times a message has been read
High read_ct (>3) = message failing repeatedly → investigate the error
Set a dead letter queue or max retry alert when read_ct exceeds threshold:

SELECT * FROM pgmq.q_embeddings_queue WHERE read_ct > 3;
-- These are stuck messages — inspect message content and fix the worker
```
